    "body": "Compilers in mixed toolchains, e.g. NAG/GCC, might require different linker prefixes. Without this, it becomes impossible to build packages requiring both C and Fortran compilers at all.\r\n\r\nAnother solution would be to override `disable_new_dtags` and `enable_new_dtags` properties in the `Nag` class so they would return empty lines.",
